This point opened my eyes to possibilities I had not considered at first.  The original consensus to live in the colony on Ayn Rand Station would have been exactly as described or the colony itself would have failed.  They had to agree on certain philosophies and ways of living to make the experiment a reality.  The first consensus had to be ‘survival of the fittest’. In order to gain consensus originally and in order to maintain the culture once it was developed all participants had to have real power or they would simply revolt.  We are not talking about ‘go quietly into the night’ types here.  Any system that did not offer real opportunity for the creation of power would not survive.  Now, inherent in this is that you have to take the power for yourself, but that is a given.<br>
<br>
We see this original consensus (Survival of the fittest) in each and every scene on screen.  Decisions to remove Culculian for repeated failures against Dylan, Guderian's failure with both Dylan and Tyr, Tyr’s attitude towards any Nietzschean he kills [Tyr]Too Slow[Tyr] shows us that the consensus of these people is first and fore most ‘Survival of the fittest’.  Harsh, just like the environments they were spawned in but ‘Life is harsh’ and the individual who does not recognize this is not around long.  <br>
